## Steps to Reproduce

Sorry for not being much help here - this just popped up in my IntelliJ event log somewhere along the way.
- I dowgraded Flutter to version 1.22.6 again while in IntelliJ.
- I started the application once more on an Android emulator.
- It may have happened then.

comment_data.body: Thanks for the report. @stevemessick possibly from https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/5333?

Hmmm. #5333 was intended to prevent this log message but this case isn't handled.

See also: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-263745

I cannot reproduce this problem. I tried starting three emulators, switching between them, and running the app on each. I also tried the Refresh option to re-build the device list. Closing and re-opening the project with all three emulators running also worked as expected.

We'll need more detailed repro steps if we're going to identify the root cause.

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
Sorry, can't help you there. I saw this error in my log. That's pretty much all I can tell you.
Sorry, didn't intend to re-open the issue. Closing it again.
